Sentencas: A La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- delta oxide was prepared using the sol-gel technique.
Titulo: Attempted preparation of La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- δ leading to an in-situ formation of manganate nanocomposites as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Instead of a pure phase, La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- delta was discovered to be a combination of La0.7Ba0.3MnO3- delta and BaMnO3.
Titulo: Attempted preparation of La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- δ leading to an in-situ formation of manganate nanocomposites as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The in-situ production of La0.7Ba0.3MnO3- delta+BaMnO3 nanocomposites enhanced the oxygen vacancy (V-O) formation compared to single-phase La0.7Ba0.3MnO3- delta or BaMnO3, providing potential benefits as a cathode for fuel cells.
Titulo: Attempted preparation of La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- δ leading to an in-situ formation of manganate nanocomposites as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Subsequently, La0.7Ba0.3MnO3- delta+BaMnO3 nanocomposites were utilized as the cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs), which significantly improved cell performance.
Titulo: Attempted preparation of La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- δ leading to an in-situ formation of manganate nanocomposites as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 700., H-SOFC with a La0.7Ba0.3MnO3- delta+BaMnO3 nanocomposite cathode achieved the highest power density (1504 mW center dot cm(-2)) yet recorded for H-SOFCs with manganate cathodes.
Titulo: Attempted preparation of La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- δ leading to an in-situ formation of manganate nanocomposites as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This performance was much greater than that of single-phase La0.7Ba0.3MnO3- delta or BaMnO3 cathode cells.
Titulo: Attempted preparation of La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- δ leading to an in-situ formation of manganate nanocomposites as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the cell demonstrated excellent working stability.
Titulo: Attempted preparation of La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- δ leading to an in-situ formation of manganate nanocomposites as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: First-principles calculations indicated that the La0.7Ba0.3MnO3- delta/BaMnO3 interface was crucial for the enhanced cathode performance.
Titulo: Attempted preparation of La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- δ leading to an in-situ formation of manganate nanocomposites as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) free energy barrier was significantly lower at the La0.7Ba0.3MnO3- delta/ BaMnO3 interface than that at the La0.7Ba0.3MnO3- delta or BaMnO3 surfaces, which explained the origin of high performance and gave a guide for the construction of novel cathodes for H-SOFCs.
Titulo: Attempted preparation of La0.5Ba0.5MnO3- δ leading to an in-situ formation of manganate nanocomposites as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
